-- Top-Ranked India Beats New Zealand in 3rd Cricket Test to Take Series 1-0
-- B y   D a n   B a y n e s
-- 2010-11-23T08:21:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/top-ranked-india-beats-new-zealand-in-3rd-cricket-test-to-take-series-1-0.html
Top-ranked India beat New Zealand by
an innings and 198 runs in the series-deciding third cricket
Test at Nagpur.  Resuming day four at 24-1 in its second innings, the
touring team slumped to 175 all out after lunch. Ishant Sharma
and  Harbhajan Singh  finished with three wickets apiece as India
sealed a 1-0 series victory following two draws.  India’s batsmen, led by  Rahul Dravid ’s 191, had laid the
platform for victory yesterday by racking up 566-8 declared in
response to New Zealand’s first-innings 193.  The teams will meet in a best-of-five one-day series
starting Nov. 28 in Guwahati.  India, which replaced South Africa as the International
Cricket Council’s  No. 1-ranked Test team  in December, then
travels to South Africa for three Test matches and five one-day
internationals. The first Test starts Dec. 16 in Centurion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
